      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Specimens drawn from same production lot; dimensional verification performed prior to testing. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison at medium risk level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single load condition (400 N axial compression with 10 mm offset per ASTM F1717). Absence of multiple load magnitudes or offset distances limits coverage of the loading envelope. This factor is below the required level and represents a known gap in the validation evidence."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
