      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Quantities of interest (construct stiffness, displacement at 2% offset yield load) are directly relevant to the ASTM F1717 acceptance criteria and to the clinical performance question of construct mechanical integrity under physiological compression-bending loading."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the ASTM F1717 test protocol used as the regulatory submission basis. The FEA ensemble was developed and validated specifically for non-cannulated pedicle screw constructs under compression-bending, matching the intended use scope for which this model has been applied in clinical research and regulatory submissions."
